labels.label: Create a session for the NDAC Manager API. The access token has a expiry time of 15min.
Filter if the response is not empty.
Get the "uat" field with the access token needed to make future requests through the NDAC Manager API. The token value is updated and uploaded to a file for future requests.
Data processing to obtain just some of the details associated with ICC IDs that determine their location and resulting binding to an access point.
List all details associated with the given list of ICC IDs.
Get the current token value from the local file.
Data processing to obtain only the ICC IDs associated with each SIM.
Python script to find out when a UE has moved to another antenna or when a new UE appears. The script compares the current location result of the UEs with the last previous result.
Publish the current result of the location of the users only when there are changes as a notification.
Filter on the output of the above Python script if there has been a mobility change in the users location or if a new user has connected.
Publish the current list of ICC IDs within a local file and Kafka topic.
Filter if the list of ICC IDs is not null.
List all active SIMS associated with the access points.
Generate credentials needed to create a user session for the NDAC Manager API.
